ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this class to another student. The instructor's style is very effective and easy to understand. The topics are very relevant to engineers in all disciplines.

This course will explain how to model the stresses in a vascular wall in two diseased conditions while understanding the causes/biology of those diseases.I would recommend this class to anyone. This class was extremely informative and educational. This class was taught by a professor that knows the material amazingly well.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I learned more about stress analysis than in three previous stress courses.
This course provided the fundamentals necessary to approach my research.
This course will be very useful for me. It has really strengthened my ability to dissect a problem and analyze it mathematically.

This course allowed me to understand in basic terms how atherosclerosis and anuerysms form and also understand how the model the stresses the vascular wall will experience.This did not contribute to my research.
